  "text": "Procedure Employed for Catalysis Studies. The Lewis acid (30 μL of 100 mM solution in CH 3 CN, 3 μmol) or Brønsted acid (30 μL of 300 mM solution in CH 3 CN, 9 μmol) was added to 1.21 mL of a 1.24 mM solution of 1 (1.5 μmol) in anhydrous CH [CITATION_1] Caution! Complete disproportionation of H 2 O 2 to oxygen and water can occur and hence the reactions should not be carried out in sealed vessels.",
